text:
Chris Kermode is a retired English male tennis player, a former tournament director and the current executive chairman & president of the Association of Tennis Professionals.
On 20 November 2013 Kermode was appointed as the ATP executive chairman & president to succeed Brad Drewett who died of an illness in May 2013.
